TITLE: Ken DeLand missing: Timeline of American college student's disappearance while studying abroad in France
SUMMARY: Ken DeLand, an American college student missing in France, hasn’t been heard from in over two weeks, but reportedly had aspirations of visiting Marseille before returning to the U.S.

TITLE: US considers sending Patriot missile defense system to Ukraine
SUMMARY: The U.S. is close to a decision on sending Ukraine its advanced Patriot missile defense system as Russia looks to acquire hundreds of ballistic missiles from Iran.

TITLE: US-Africa Leaders Summit: Washington ‘playing catch-up’ with Russia and China
SUMMARY: The Biden Administration is attempting to court Africa’s 1.3 billion people at this week's U.S.-Africa Summit in Washington, D.C., the first U.S. summit in eight years.

TITLE: Trial for Chinese Communist Party critic Jimmy Lai postponed nearly a year after lawyer's visa denied
SUMMARY: Chinese Communist Party critic Jimmy Lai will not stand trial for national security charges until September of 2023 due to ongoing challenges with his British lawyer's visa.

TITLE: Ukraine economy to take $700B hit over war with Russia
SUMMARY: Ukraine's economy is on track to take a $700 billion hit following 10 months of war with Russia by the year's end.

TITLE: China advises citizens in Afghanistan to leave 'as soon as possible' following hotel bombing in Kabul
SUMMARY: China is telling its citizens to leave Afghanistan following a hotel bombing in Kabul. The hotel that was bombed in Kabul was Chinese-owned.

TITLE: Cuban authorities intercept migrant raft sporting American flag in broad daylight
SUMMARY: Cuba's coast guard intercepted passengers from an American flag-adorned raft Monday, confusing onlookers in nearby Havana — most attempted escapes from the nation are made in secrecy.

TITLE: China struggles to dismantle controversial 'zero COVID' policies
SUMMARY: Chinese officials have abandoned the nation's exceedingly strict and controversial "zero COVID" policies following national unrest, though reform is proving difficult.

TITLE: Church of England receives petition to scrap 'deeply damaging and wrong' transgender guidance for children
SUMMARY: A petition urging the Church of England to scrap its transgender-affirming guidance for primary schools was given to Archbishop of Canterbury Justin Welby on Monday.

TITLE: Police raid European Parliament as investigators probe Qatar bribery allegations
SUMMARY: European Parliament has been the scene of multiple raids by Belgian police investigating alleged corruption and bribery related to the Qatari government.
